dh(\theta)=dg\bigl(f(\theta)\bigr)\circ df(\theta)\ .
h'(\theta)= dh(\theta).1=dg\bigl(f(\theta)\bigr)\circ df(\theta).1 =dg\bigl(f(\theta)\bigr).f'(\theta)\ .
\bigl[dg\bigr]_{x,y,z)}=\left[\matrix{{\partial\xi\over\partial x}&{\partial\xi\over\partial y}&{\partial\xi\over\partial z} \cr {\partial\eta\over\partial x}&{\partial\eta\over\partial y}&{\partial\eta\over\partial z}\cr}\right]_{(x,y,z)} =\left[\matrix{1/z&0&-x/z^2 \cr 0 &1/z&-y/z^2\cr}\right]\ .
